article.description: Ty Charles tied his career high with 22 points and Stephen F. Austin defeated Our Lady of the Lake 95-56 Saturday night for the Lumberjacks' fifth consecutive victory.
article.headline: Stephen F. Austin defeats Our Lady of the Lake 95-56
article.linkText: Stephen F. Austin defeats Our Lady of the Lake 95-56
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Ty Charles tied his career high with 22 points and Stephen F. Austin defeated Our Lady of the Lake 95-56 Saturday night for the Lumberjacks' fifth consecutive victory. Demetrious Floyd added 13 points and T.J. Holyfield and Clide Geffrard 11 apiece with Geffrard grabbing 10 rebounds for his second straight double-double. The NAIA Division-II Saints (5-4) came in averaging 99.6 points per game but shot just 34.5 percent. Averaging 13.6 3-points baskets, they were 6 of 21 Saturday. They had 23 turnovers, 17 on steals. Joe Jackson led the Saints with 20 points. The Lumberjacks (7-3) shot 50.7 percent despite hitting just 3 of 16 from long range. They made 24 of 34 free throws. The Lumberjacks, who normally play in William R. Johnson Coliseum, went across campus to play in Shelton Gymnasium for the first time since Feb. 28, 1974. Shelton was the program's home from 1951-74.
